se that conformed to the pedagogical and philosophical norms of Leiden University’s medical faculty. In doing so, Boerhaave gave his chemistry a coherent organizational structure and philosophical foundation and thus transformed an artisanal practice into an academic discipline. Inventing Chemistry is essential reading for historians of chemistry, medicine, and academic life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBoerhaave, Herman, -- 1668-1738. 0aChemistry -- History. 0aChemistry -- Study and teaching -- Netherlands -- Leiden -- History -- 18th century. 0aChemistryxHistory. 0aChemistryxStudy and teachingzNetherlandszLeidenxHistoryy18th century. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022667760640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226677620423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226677620/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles